
[1]murder

   MUR'DER, n. [L. mors.]

   1. The act of unlawfully killing a human being with premeditated
   malice, by a person of sound mind. To constitute murder in law, the
   person killing another must be of sound mind or in possession of his
   reason, and the act must be done with malice prepense, aforethought or
   premeditated; but malice may be implied, as well as express.

   2. An outcry, when life is in danger.

                                MUR'DER, v.t.

   1. To kill a human being with premeditated malice. [See the Noun.]

   2. To destroy; to put an end to.

   Canst thou murder thy breath in middle of a word?
